content:
@everyone, SEB pushed a new update this morning that advanced VM detection.

Until further notice, don't use it on SEB.

Patch will likely come out in the next few days.

@everyone, very important announcement, please read:

Evadus+ is currently not working with Respondus. I have had 8 people confirm that it does work for them, HOWEVER, I have 3 people report to me that it didn't work for them. Therefore, for the safety of my users, Respondus will be delisted as a compatible proctor until I can 100% guarantee it works for EVERYONE, not just some people.

That being said, I have paid 2 reverse engineers $1300 to decompile Respondus to see exactly how they detect VM's and Sandboxes. They gave me a timeline of 4-6 days, so in about 8 days we will have a patch ready. Everyone that writes on Respondus gets a free month as compensation.

WEBCAM PROBLEMS:
If you are having problems using a webcam, I posted a video in <#1362037965668487238> that largely fixes it. This new method is superior in many ways, however also has some drawbacks. I am going to start a project that will use this superior method and get rid of it's drawbacks, it's a significant task, however I'll get it done.

ALSO: We have a very big update shipping tomorrow (Evadus and Evadus Lite), so stay tuned.


Alright, that's the most important news, however I also have some other things that I want to say.


Thank you, and I genuinely mean it, to everyone that supports this project. I didn't expect at all to have this supportive and patient of a community. I thought that if I made one single mistake, everyone would hate me for it. However, you have been incredibly supportive and helpful, and I genuinely cannot thank you enough.

There is a lot of stress and pressure that comes with such an ambitious project, more than most people realize. However, with God as my witness, I promise each and every one of you here that I do my utmost best each day to keep building each one of our tools. This project is all I think about every day, new features, fixes, improvements etc. I quit my entire life to pursue this project. I left my university (more like expelled really), left my social life, quit my job, left my girlfriend and sacrificed a lot more than I get admit on discord message, so believe me when I say that I am very dedicated.

I'd also like to thank the people that have helped me so far.

@null has made all of our cheating videos so far. He has helped me get the Evadus tool and the main app into the stable state it is in today. He has also been around here since day 1.
@null has helped me improve the discord server massively.
@null is our biggest patron, and most active user of Evadus, and gives lots of feedback on the tool.

@everyone  IMPORTANT NOTE FOR RESPONDUS USERS:

To get it working for Respondus, YOU HAVE TO RUN THE CUSTOMIZER POWERSHELL SCRIPT!

Also, it is going to say something about your date time not being correct, simply go into the settings inside of the VM, and mess with the datetime and timezone sync settings

@everyone , new tutorial video for Evadus+ on the Youtube channel, sorry if I'm slow to respond to anyone, I've got the flu

<#1362037965668487238> is going to be the new channel for showcasing tutorials.

I am going to be remaking the tutorial video for Evadus, not happy with how it turned out

@everyone , Gemini 2.5 Pro is now fully functional!

For those curious why this took so long (5 days), it's because it's VERY poorly documented on how to switch to the new Google AI SDK, which is required to use Gemini 2.5 Pro. Despite it being almost 7 months since GA (General availability), it has the most abominable documentation ever.

But alas, it is done, thank fuck.
